# Student Management System (Version 1)

A simple Java-based Student Management System developed as a Class 12 school project. This project demonstrates the use of core Java concepts such as Object-Oriented Programming (OOP), file handling, collections, and menu-driven applications.

## Features
- Add new student records
- View all student records
- Search for a student
- Update student details
- Delete student records
- Store data using file handling
- Menu-driven console interface

## Technologies Used
- Java
- ArrayList
- File Handling (BufferedReader & BufferedWriter)
- OOP Concepts (Classes, Objects, Encapsulation)

## Version 1 Goals
This version focuses on building a functional and beginner-friendly student management system while applying fundamental Java programming concepts learned in Class 12.

## Future Improvements (Version 2)
Planned upgrades include:
- Graphical User Interface (GUI) using Java Swing
- Database integration (MySQL)
- Student sorting and filtering options
- Improved search functionality
- Attendance management
- Grade and report card generation
- Better error handling and validation

## Educational Purpose
This project was created for learning and practice purposes to strengthen Java programming, file handling, and software development skills.

